				<h1>Snowblower Tachometer</h1>
				<p>Welcome to the snowblower-rev-counter web site</p>
				<p>In this project we want to design and build a tachometer (revolution counter) for a very old snowblower.</p>
				<p>The goal of this project is not to build something useful, it is rather to let my 15 year old son acquire some knowledge in the following fields:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Basic analog and digital electronic design</li>
					<li>Arduino programming</li>
					<li>3D design and printing</li>
					<li>Planning a project and being involved in the different steps from the beginning to the end</li>
				</ul>
				<h1>Sub-projects</h1>
				<p>This project is divided in the following sub-projects:</p>
				<ul>
					<SUBPROJECT text="High level project design" href="design.html"/>
					<SUBPROJECT text="Getting rotation information from the engine" href="rotation-information.html"/>
